Sector
Hotel
Job Level
Non-Management
Controls room status in order to obtain the maximum room revenue with maximum occupancy and service quality to provide guest satisfaction.
Updates Front Office information board as often as necessary.
Ensures the circulation of memos and flow of information within the department is going smoothly.
Carries out a thorough shift handover at the beginning and end of each shift and checks that all items requiring attention are detailed in reception logbook and initialed once completed, ensure the same is followed by all GSAs.
Supervises all activities of Front Desk colleagues and assigns duties as needed to the different areas within the department.
Ensure CID is sent on time and focuses on a strong follow up and extra attention to the Police requirements in sending guest information as per provided standards, assuring no fines are received.
Anticipates sold out situations and knows how many rooms are overbooked.
